## Proposal
I know [docs](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/widgets/WidgetsApp/backButtonDispatcher.html) mentions:

> If this is not provided, the widgets app will create a [RootBackButtonDispatcher](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/widgets/RootBackButtonDispatcher-class.html) by default.

However it shouldn't be recreated every time.

Possible implementation:
```dart
class WidgetsApp extends StatefulWidget {
  final BackButtonDispatcher? backButtonDispatcher;

  WidgetsApp.router({
    Key? key,
    this.backButtonDispatcher,
  }) : super(key: key);

  @override
  _WidgetsAppState createState() => _WidgetsAppState();
}

class _WidgetsAppState extends State<WidgetsApp> {
  late final _defaultBackButtonDispatcher = RootBackButtonDispatcher();

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    Widget? routing;
    if (_usesRouter) {
      routing = Router<Object>(
        backButtonDispatcher: widget.backButtonDispatcher ?? _defaultBackButtonDispatcher,
      );
    }
    // ...
  }
}
```

Developing nested Routers, this issue could cause some headaches if someone assumes `RootbackButtonDispatcher` remain the same during the app's run and already called `deferTo` / `takePriority` methods on `ChildBackButtonDispatcher`.

Note: not only `RouterDelegate.notifyListerners` can ask Router for reporting a new url, someone might use some state management around `MaterialApp.router` and [providing new RouterDelegate instance for it](https://github.com/flutter/flutter/blob/2.10.0/packages/flutter/lib/src/widgets/router.dart#L613) or use `InheritedWidget.of` call inside [`RouterDelegate.build`](https://github.com/flutter/flutter/blob/2.10.0/packages/flutter/lib/src/widgets/router.dart#L586) and in the latter two cases `backButtonDispatcher` will be recreated more often.

